    "body": "How do I make sure that 2 messages are delivered in the same order? For example, I have this code:\r\n```\r\n$wmessage1 = $w->sendMessage($destinationPhone, \"ABC\");\r\n$wmessage2 = $w->sendMessage($destinationPhone, \"DEF\");\r\n```\r\nSometimes, the 2nd message reaches the client first, and the client sees:\r\nDEF\r\nABC\r\n\r\nIs there a good way to make sure that the messages are delivered in order (other than putting a short delay between the statements like this: )\r\n```\r\n$wmessage1 = $w->sendMessage($destinationPhone, \"ABC\");\r\nusleep(100000); /* Sleep 1/10th of a second */\r\n$wmessage2 = $w->sendMessage($destinationPhone, \"DEF\");\r\n```",
    "closed_at": null,
